  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Magdalena river basin, which is home to 49% of the Colombian population and recieves the direct wastewater discharge from 128 municipalities, is now recognized as legal entity. This project seeks to consolidate the Citizen Observatory of Water Justice in Colombia by monitoring critical points of the Magdalena river across the country, training  grassroots organizations in water quality monitoring and legal procedures to protect the rights of the river and other water bodies in the country.</narrative>
  </description>
